<Layout title="Introduction to Ragas | Harmonium Halt"
  description="Understand the complete framework of Indian ragas — the soul of classical music. Free harmonium lesson with interactive web harmonium tool.">
  <div class="bg-white border-b" style="border-color:rgba(28,16,8,.08)">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-2.5 breadcrumb">
      <a href="/">Home</a><span class="mx-1.5">›</span>
      <a href="/lessons">Lessons</a><span class="mx-1.5">›</span>
      <span>Introduction to Ragas</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-8 sm:py-12">
    <div class="mb-6 sm:mb-8">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 mb-4">
        <span class="badge badge-intermediate capitalize">intermediate</span>
        <span class="text-xs" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.4);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">⏱ 25 min · Intermediate</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="section-title text-2xl sm:text-3xl lg:text-4xl mb-3" style="color:#1c1008">Introduction to Ragas</h1>
      <p class="text-sm sm:text-base leading-relaxed" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.6);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">Understand the complete framework of Indian ragas — the soul of classical music.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="rounded-xl p-4 sm:p-5 mb-6 border" style="background:#fef9f0;border-color:rgba(212,146,10,.25)">
      <h3 class="font-bold text-sm mb-3" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">📌 Key Takeaways</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-1.5">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Raga is not just a scale — it is a complete musical personality</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Aroha = ascending scale, Avaroha = descending</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Vadi = most important note, Samvadi = second most important</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Pakad = characteristic phrase that identifies the raga</li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-xs sm:text-sm" style="color:#92400e;font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif"><svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Each raga has a traditional time of day for performance</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="prose-hm">
      <h2>What is a Raga</h2>
      <p>A raga is a complete musical framework governing which notes to use how to move between them which notes to emphasize characteristic phrases that define it and when to perform it. The Sanskrit word raga comes from ranj meaning to color or please. A raga colors the mind of the listener with a specific emotional quality called rasa — peace devotion longing joy or grandeur.</p>

      <h2>Key Raga Terms</h2>
      <p>Aroha (ascending scale), Avaroha (descending scale), Vadi (the most important and frequently used note), Samvadi (second most important note usually a fourth or fifth from Vadi), Pakad (short characteristic phrase that instantly identifies the raga), Rasa (the emotional quality evoked), Prahar (the traditional time of day for performance), and Thaat (the parent scale from which the raga is derived).</p>

      <h2>Raga Time Theory</h2>
      <p>Indian music has a beautiful system where each raga belongs to a specific time of day. Early morning ragas like Bhairav and Todi evoke devotional seriousness. Morning ragas like Bhairavi have gentle tender quality. Evening ragas like Yaman are romantic and expansive. Late night ragas like Darbari are deeply serious and grand. This is not mere tradition but reflects how sounds affect the mind at different times.</p>

      <h2>Your First Raga Yaman</h2>
      <p>Raga Yaman is the recommended first raga. It is performed at evening sunset time evokes a romantic yearning mood and has a clear unambiguous identity. Aroha: N R G M' P D N upper-S. Avaroha: upper-S N D P M' G R S. Defining feature: Tivra Ma (F sharp) is always used — natural Ma never appears in Yaman. Vadi: Ga. Pakad: N R G comma M' G R S.</p>

      <h2>How to Approach a Raga</h2>
      <p>Step 1 listen to the raga performed by a master on YouTube. Step 2 memorize the aroha and avaroha until automatic. Step 3 master the pakad. Step 4 practice slow exploration of the raga's notes. Step 5 learn a simple composition (bandish). This sequence from listening to playing deeply mirrors how traditional musicians have always learned.</p>

    </div>
    <div class="mt-8 mb-6">
      <h2 class="font-display font-bold text-xl sm:text-2xl mb-3" style="color:#1c1008">Practice Now</h2>
      <p class="text-xs sm:text-sm mb-4" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.5);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif">Apply what you just learned on the interactive harmonium below.</p>
      <div class="rounded-2xl p-4 sm:p-6" style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#1c1008,#3d1a08)">
        <Harmonium/>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-col xs:flex-row items-stretch xs:items-center justify-between gap-3 mt-8 pt-6 border-t" style="border-color:rgba(28,16,8,.08)">
      <a href="/lessons" class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm" style="color:rgba(28,16,8,.5);font-family:'Plus Jakarta Sans',sans-serif;text-decoration:none">
        <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M19 12H5M12 5l-7 7 7 7"/></svg>
        All Lessons
      </a>
      <a href="/practice" class="btn-primary justify-center text-center">Open Full Practice Tool →</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>